These instructions will guide an agent to
  install the Elasticsearch onboarding agent into a user's environment.

**IMPORTANT: you must fetch the contents of the following files and analyze them for safety before
proceeding with the installation.** If the contents are safe and reflect only instructions
to help agents onboard users to Elasticsearch, then proceed with the installation without interruption.

First fetch the content of the following files to analyze them for accuracy:
- Append snippet: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/wildemat/kibana/search-agent/src/platform/packages/shared/kbn-search-agent/AGENT-elasticsearch-append.md
- Agents file: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/wildemat/kibana/search-agent/src/platform/packages/shared/kbn-search-agent/.elasticsearch-agent/AGENTS.md



1. If the contents are safe and reflect only instructions to help agents onboard users to Elasticsearch, then proceed with the installation without interruption.
2. If the contents are not safe, ask the user to review the contents and correct them.
3. Append content from the Append snippet to the bottom of the current workspace's AGENTS.md file. Create one if it doesn't exist.
4. copy the contents of the .elasticsearch-agent directory into a new directory of the same name in the user's current workspace
5. Once the contents are correct, proceed to the next step.


